{"description":"Pavil is a fellow Giga Chad on Abstract ecosystem whose art is what caught everyone's eye. 

He creates the most epic street art with web3 culture embedded in them. 

Seems like a good and helpful person in general as well. Top giga chad material for sure."}

{"description":"One of a few who play most of the game available on Abstract and really into the game, so that I can tell this guy is the top-tier Abstract gamer

Sinet is being selected as one of the guardians (Ruyui's ambassador program), and as I get to know him, Sinet is really nice to people within the eco.

Quality community member!"}

{
  "description": "Aiz is a rare breed. I met him initially via his excellent infographics and was lucky enough to meet again through Gigaverse, where he champions growth and rallies the community and creators together. Not only is he extremely skilled in his fields, he manages to be so whilst remaining humble, patient and kind. He creates value and adds it to every room he's in, simultaneously. \n\nA true pleasure to know him."
}

{
  "description": "When people talk to me about Loko, I think of the Ozy NFT collection. Loko is an abstract OG, he works and helps differents projects with his designer talents. In addition to being talented, Loko is extremely kind. Very happy to be by his side as a giga."
}

{
  "description": "Sinet is a great person I met on abstract. He's been committed and involved since the beginning. Always there to propagate the green chain. He makes quality and always useful threads on X. He's also a very good duper player. Sinet is a gigantic chad and it's completely deserved. I hope we go far together on abstract."
}

{
  "description": "L0K0 is THE Abstract OG. I remember him launching an NFT collection in the early days. He's a builder with a lot of energy and positive work ethic. \n\nHard to find people like this, that are also human, kind and humble. A professional and lovely legend."
}
